title: The History of England from the Tudors to the Stuarts
description:
Audio Books : Misc. Educational : MP3/mono/32k : English


This course surveys the history of England during the early-modern period from 1485 to 1714.

The backbone of the course is a narrative of high politics, but it also incorporates social, economic, and cultural history, including the histories of religion, the family, women, poverty, crime, and the arts.
